name: Celegian
description: Super-intelligent jellyfish-like people who speak telepathically, and possess a natural form of telekinesis which allows them to float above the ground

name: D6 Unit
description: D6 utility droids were created to assist navigators and engineers aboard spacecraft. This particular model became popular do to their proclivity towards quirky and social personalities.

name: Dulok
description: Troublemakers from the dingiest swamps of Endor, Duloks are the ancient enemy of the Ewoks, and have a reputation of being greedy and foul-tempered.

name: Gorax
description: The people eating giants of Endor. Gorax are mostly sentient recluses who build their homes in mountains and caves.

name: Hutt
description: Large, Sluglike crime lords from the Planet Nal Hutta. They are tough and hardy, though generations of debauchery have slowed them down.

name: Icehead
description: Sharp-clawed servants of the Snow King, one of the four seasonal rulers of Endor.

name: Kowakian
description: Rude little bastards from the planet Kowak. They're rude, freaky, and just downright unpleasant. Seriously, nobody want to be around these guys.

name: Lamproid
description: A serpentine, carnivorous species from Florn. Lamproids are frequently mistaken as non-sentient due to their frightening appearance and lack ofart or culture of any kind, however they are capab;e of speaking basic.

name: Mirialan
description: The people from the planet Mirial are known for their deep religious tradition and a natural connection to the force.

name: Ortolan
description: Stocky Bipeds from the Planet Orto. They have developed a thick skin and keen senses in order to survive the harsh climates of Orto.

name: Paaerduag
description: Weird symbionts from the planet Sorjus. They are born as seperate creatures but then fuse together later in life.

name: Pa'lowick
description: Shy amphibious creatures from the marshy coasts of the planet Lowick. The Pa'lowick are a very traditional culture who records their history through song

name: Patitite
description: The Small Natives of Patitite Patuna, ruled by the Militant "Big." Some have escaped the soldier's lifestyle, however, by becoming entertainers and getting off planet.

name: Shistavanen
description: A wolflike species from the planet Uvena Prime. Most Shistavanen are extremely isolationist by nature, but a minority were more outgoing, prefering to travel hyperspace lanes and meet new people.

name: Toydarian
description: Master salesman from the swamps of Toydaria. they have become resistant to force suggestion do o evolving alongside psychic Swamp Pixies, who would lure unsuspecting prey with the force

name: Dweller
description: aquatic citizens of Endor's Underwater Kingdom who subsist entirely on special food pearls

name: Yuzzum
description: Yuzzum originate on the Forest Moon of Endor, using their long limbs to run down Ruggers on the scattered plains. They are also known for their beautiful voices and musical language,

name: Zilkin
description: Small amphibious beings who, despite their diminutive stature, possess remarkable athletic,  sstrategic, and mechanical skills.

name: Cleaning Droid
description: NPC ONLY

name: Creature
description: NPC ONLY

name: H'nemthe
description: The H'nemthe is a creative species with a beaklike nose and four vestigial conelets on their heads. There are twenty females for every male, which has led to a tradition where single H'nemthe women travel the galaxy in search for love when they come of age.

name: Ithorian
description: Natives of the planet Ithor, the Ithorians are one of the most intelligent races in the universe, they are however very weak and struggle in melee combat.

name: Thisspiasian
description: The snake-like thisspiasians may appear to outsiders to exist in a permanent state of calm, but on their rocky home planet of Thisspias they are passionate warriors and brutal hunters

name: Letter for Dice
text: To my lovely wife, Dice Ibegon, I'm so sorry. Your commitment was always greater than mine. I just couldn't stop thinking about you being all alone in the ice. It ruined me. I met a friend on Nal hutta who helped me realize I wasn't helping anything. I'm going back to Manaan now, Love. Maybe I'll kill some sith for you. We'll get em. I know I'll see you again one day, and until then, you'll be in my heart.

name: Letter for Lak
text: To my husband Lak, It's so cold here. We set up camp in a cave not far from the landing site. Most of the time you can't see anything past the blowing snow, but every now and then it calms down and you can take in the view of the mountains against the beautiful sky. We've been hearing strange sounds coming through the ice walls. We think it's some sort of life form, so we're going to try and break through the ice to try and identify them. I hope their not working you too hard in the storage rooms. Can't wait to see you when I get back and give you a pat on the head.

text: I understand. It's probably kind of awkward. We can find someone else.
Our real name is unpronouncable without two mouths and unhearable without four ears.
Thanks for listening, %PCName, it feels good to tell her story

Dice was assigned on a special mission, to scout the planet Hoth for a location to build a secret Republic base. She and her crew set out and after they landed we never heard from them again. I waited for months hoping for her miraculous return, but when it became clear she was gone, then I decided to get gone too. I hopped on the nearest ship and got as far away as I could. Dreddon's been good to me and now I'm a half decent shot, but I would do anything for one last six armed hug from Dice Ibegon.

One, I was a shit bounty hunter and that wasn't going to change anytime soon. Two, I would fight my way through hundreds of mandolorians just to spend a day with Dice. When her shuttle came to pick her up I decided I would tag along. 
   We were stationed on Manaan, Dice would fly shipments from base to base, I tracked inventory. Two years later we got married. Three months after that the Sith returned.

Five years ago we met in a cantina on Tatooine. I was there looking for a bounty when my real treasure slithered in. Her name was Dice Ibegon, and she had the most beautiful mandibles you could ever dream of. I bought her a drink and we got to talking. Turns out she was a Republic fighter pilot visiting some academy friends while she was on leave. I kept thinking of two things during that conversation.
Nal Hutta is the glorious jewel sitting at the center of Hutt space. I hope you find our home to your liking.
I see you!
-----TSAESCI VOICEFILES START HERE-----
You have no right to come here!
You have no right to come here!

Do you have the credits from Narva yet?
Those sith are really something. Good thing this is a Czerka town instead. Did Narva scrounge up the credits for the water tax?

A H'nemthe woman named M'iiyoom Onith has just missed her flight to Gamorr because she couldn't afford the travel tax. She's sulking in the spacesport right now, see if you can keep things from escalating.
M'iiyoom must have really liked my sandwiches to pay for me to travel out here.
That sandwich was delicious!
Oh it's delicious! I've been starving all day. Thank you so much, could you please get me some booze too?
It sounds good right? Not one with meat though, it's a tradition among my people that we don't eat meat until *Coooo* our first time *CoooOOOO* mating.
There's no truer way to a person's heart than one of my sandwiches.
That's Me!
He's a real great guy, and an even better cook.
At first I was nervous that I would never find anyone, but after *Cooo* spendig the day with you, it seems like maybe I'm incredibly charming

The Pursuit is what we call it when a H'nemthe woman travels the galaxy in search of a mate. H'nemthe Women vastly outnumber the men, so if we're still single when we come of age then it's traditional to go on Pursuit.
I'm Gurkhob. My brother is Balch.
Gurkhob is my brother. I'm Balch.

My son Gurkhob has always been an impressive specimen. didn't help him when it came to girls, though.
